
[1]granitic

   GRANIT'IC, a. Pertaining to granit; like granit; having the nature of
   granitic; as granitic texture.

   1. Consisting of granit; as granitic mountains.

    Granitic aggregates, in mineralogy, granular compounds of two or more
     simple minerals, in which only one of the essential ingredients of
     granit is present; as quartz and hornblend, feldspar and shorl, &c.
   Similar compounds occur, in which none of the ingredients of granit are
                                  present.
